Taiwan Power Co. plans to invest over NT $10 billion in wind power generation over the next decade, focusing on coastal regions.
This initiative aligns with the government's eco-friendly policy.
In the US, Senator Edward Kennedy opposes offshore wind projects, advocating for a national policy.
Meanwhile, Long Island Power Authority aims to build 40 wind turbines to meet renewable energy targets.
Studies show the impact of wind farms on local meteorology, emphasizing the need for comprehensive regulations.
Globally, the shift towards renewable energy sources like wind power is gaining momentum, with countries like Denmark leading the way.
